    Reference

    All functions

    calc_dist()

    Calculate distance to a feature

    clone_estimATM()

    Clone estimATM repository

    convert_length()

    Convert CPS length

    estimate_bootstrap()

    Calculate bootstrap estimates of species biomass

    estimate_inshore()

    Extract acoustic intervals for nearshore extrapolation

    estimate_length()

    Estimate CPS length

    estimate_point()

    Calculate point estimate of species biomass

    estimate_ts()

    Estimate target strength of CPS from total length

    estimate_weight()

    Estimate CPS weight

    extract_cal()

    Extract calibration results from .txt or .xml files.

    extract_cal_ecs()

    Extract calibration results from Echoview calibration supplement (.ecs) files.

    extract_cal_fm()

    Extract calibration results from calibrations in FM-mode.

    extract_cps_nasc()

    Estimate CPS backscatter in Echoview CSV files

    extract_csv()

    Extract vertically integrated backscatter from CSV files

    extract_ctd_cast()

    Extract cast data from CTD and UCTD casts.

    extract_ctd_header()

    Extract header information from CTD and UCTD casts.

    extract_gps()

    Create gps.csv files used by Echoview.

    fancy_sci()

    Format ggplot2 axis labels to fancy scientific.

    find_hull()

    Draw convex hull polygon around a collection of points

    get_basemap()

    Create basemap

    is.nan(<df>)

    Identify NaN values in a data frame.

    map_bounds()

    Calculate map boundaries from lat/lon input.

    project_df()

    Project a data frame with geographic coordinates to a different coordinate reference system (CRS) while retaining the original coordinates.

    project_sf()

    Convert simple feature to data frame with a different coordinate reference system (CRS).

    scs2dd()

    Convert latitude or longitude from SCS format to decimal degrees

    scs2posix()

    Convert date and time from SCS format to POSIXct

    xtrct()

    Extract nodes from XML file.

    xtrct_df()

    Extract child nodes and values from node list.
